generally speaking, Flash+Protean Hulk -> Body Double*+Viscera Seer, copy Protean Hulk. (*Also Karmic Guide if you're running white). It also works in Meren, basically giving Meren its own version of Boonweaver combo: Sidisi+Viscera Seer, get Reanimate, reanimate Protean Hulk, sac to get Eternal Witness, get Reanimate back, Reanimate Protean sac to get Mikaeus, sac EWit bring back to get Reanimate again, reanimate Protean again sac to get Triskelion and win. Needs an additional 3 black and sorcery speed though.
Aw, c'mon
also requires like, uh, 19 life.
wait no 21.
Why reanimate vs animate dead?
Harder to remove
What do you mean?
Reanimate is a sorcery vs animate dead being an enchantment. If animate dead is blown up you lose the creature you brought back
I mean instant speed ruins the exploit trigger. But the main reason is because reanimate combo is BBB + 21 life instead of 3BBB, which when we're talking about a 7cmc combo card, is really relevant.
instant speed enchantment removal that is.
Ok the cost I can see but saying an enchantment is harder to remove I don't agree with. Far more likely for folks to have instant speed creature removal than enchantment.

oh, actually with the EWit fetch you can get Blood Artist to mitigate some of the life loss. It should cost a net of like, 19 life because you sac protean hulk (gain a life), get mikaeus and sac ewit (gain another life).
actually even better, the 6th mana can go to a mana dork that you just sac to viscera seer to gain a life. so 18 life, 3 black, and sorcery speed.
You could also run this in Abzan and have soul sisters or Trostani etc.
well, with Karador the combo doesnt require Reanimate shenanigans and all that life because of Karmic Guide.
I'm just thinking for Meren, which is GB, how you'd win with Protean Hulk.
Ah. Gotcha.
Karmic Guide->Viscera Seer can get like, Reveilark, and so on. Requires no additional mana, plays through Rule of Law/Eidolon of Rhetoric effects too.
but without white things get trickier.
I'm not sure if there's a more efficient way to combo than that in GB. It's possible to play something like Basal Sliver and fetch alongside EWit so that the combo only requires B
but Basal Sliver is not a commonly played card in Meren.
to be honest, if I made my entire Meren deck a combo engine with Protean Hulk though, I would totally consider playing Basal Sliver. Because why not, if the deck is that linear.
Hrm...honestly you could just use Strionic Res to copy the death trigger and go get Mike & Trike for just 2 Colorless and be done.
but then you need to run Strionic Res :stuck_out_tongue:
Thought of another one, if you have a recurrable sac outlet out already, you can just get Mikaeus and Walking Ballista.
Mikaeus is 6, ballista is 0. that works.
Ballista needs mana to do anything. You have to double the +1 counter it gets from Mike to kill the table.
not with a sac outlet.
Sure

So actually just thought, the combo only costs 7 life! Because first you get Sidisi+Viscera Seer, then you reanimate Protean sac to Viscera Seer, get Mikaeus Ballista. Sac Ballista, get a +1+1 on it, ping someone, sac again.
So lots of ways to get the same old two card combo :heart_eyes:
Yup
yeah. I'm trying to think what's the "most efficient way." Seems like only requiring 1 additional black mana is the most efficient way.
or not even requiring additional black if you already have the recurrable sac outlet.
Pod+Seer is the setup I always imagined it would. E
Be
I dunno...my 2 Colorless and no life way seems more efficient. :scream:
Pardon...2 generic
Yea, watch that heresy!
I think the main issue with it is that you need to run Strionic Resonator in a deck that may or may not always want it. Reanimate, Viscera Seer and Sidisi are already cards Meren wants.
actually it's 4 colorless if you dont have strionic out.
But I mean it works. It's definitely another viable route.
also Strionic is untutorable realistically
I ran Strionic in Meren to double her trigger.
that's definitely legit. The issue is how do you combo out without it? I think the Reanimate line is the way.
Sidisi+Viscera Reanimate re-sac etc.
or Mikaeus+Ballista.
In Black? Everything is tutorable.
sure but, I mean the point is, maybe you don't have Demonic Tutor or something in your hand, or don't have as much mana. It's more restrictive.
That applies across the board here.
Always if...but the real point is all of the options are viable and not mutually restrictive.

Not really. My protean hulk line requires: recurrable sac outlet, or a one-time sac outlet + 1 black + aforementioned cards already in your deck. Your line requires a sac outlet + 2 mana + strionic already out + aforementioned cards in deck. Requires the extra card out.
I agree with that last sentence!
Lots of ways to make it work :slightly_smiling_face:
Mine doesn't require reanimate so actually break even on cards.

actually forgot Phyrexian Delver is a card, so Sidisi isnt needed. But anyway, Sidisi tutors for the Reanimate, then you use it. It doesn't require spending additional cards or breaking even or whatever. Besides, if you win the game you don't need card advantage.
Phyrexian Delver + Viscera Seer bring back Protean works. Costs 0 black mana. OK, that's even better.

so literally your hand can be empty, board can be empty entirely except for a Phyrexian Tower and Protean Hulk. And you'll win off what I mentioned. The advantage are that and the fact that it only requires cards that arent dead (except Ballista) (not to imply Strionic is dead of course). It's a compact line. Strionic Resonator also works, but it's another card in the combo that you need to have out when it starts-- which makes it a bit less compact.
